<paragraph id="8BAB3822FF9DFF93FF5AF8484EC4340A" blockId="2.[151,1436,1932,2029]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,285]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="165" pageId="2" pageNumber="164">
<taxonomicName id="4C1443A1FF9DFF92FF5AF8484E1D32FB" box="[199,323,2004,2028]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="164" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fulvipes">
<emphasis id="B960E430FF9DFF92FF5AF8484E1D32FB" box="[199,323,2004,2028]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="164">M. fulvipes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was previously known from only a single specimen collected in northern 
<collectingCountry id="F30378B2FF9DFF92FBE7F8494B8732FA" box="[1146,1241,2004,2029]" name="Vietnam" pageId="2" pageNumber="164">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF8545D3FF9DFF93FB7AF8494F8A35A7" author="Kallies" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="165" pageId="2" pageNumber="164" refString="Kallies, A. &amp; Arita, Y. (2004) New taxa and records of clearwing moths of the tribe Melittiini (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae) from Vietnam. Japanese Journal of Systematic Entomology, 10 (2), 193 - 209." type="journal article" year="2004">Kallies &amp; Arita, 2004</bibRefCitation>
). It is here recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="F30378B2FF9CFF93FE6FFF0A4D6B35A7" box="[498,565,151,176]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="165">China</collectingCountry>
for the first time. It can be recognized by the brownish ochre hairs on the hind leg, its wide discal spot of the forewing with its very short projection into the anterior transparent area, the broad apical area. It is further characterized by its genitalia (
<figureCitation id="132F24A7FF9CFF93FD61FF424C1F35EF" box="[764,833,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 9, 10" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1974,1997]" captionTargetBox="[220,1366,203,1918]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[190,1375,193,1938]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 9, 10. Male genitalia of Melittiini from China. 9. Melittia fulvipes (Gen. Prep. AK 740, SCAU). 10. Macroscelesia perlucida sp. nov., paratype (Gen. Prep. AK 744, SCAU)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192925/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="165">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), which display a short and broad valva, with a short and broad ventral lobe.
</paragraph>
